physical_examinations.relevant_findings: External examination showed no ectrodactyly or lobster-claw deformity. There were no positive signs of ectodermal dysplasia (sparse hair, nail dysplasia, abnormal teeth, lacrimal duct obstruction, sweat gland dysplasia, etc.). The external examination was consistent with the gestational age of the fetus. Autopsy confirmed bilateral cleft lip and palate (bilateral cleft lip, alveolar cleft, and complete cleft palate), right renal dysplasia, and hydronephrosis of the left kidney.
